objecttypes.name: AbstractWorkProductComponent
objecttypes.description: Generic reference object containing the universal properties of a Work Product Component for inclusion in data type specific Work Product Component objects

properties.name: Name
properties.description: Name

properties.name: Description
properties.description: Description.  Summary of the work product component.  Not the same as Remark which captures thoughts of creator about the wpc.

properties.name: CreationDateTime
properties.description: Date that a resource (work  product component here) is formed outside of OSDU before loading (e.g. publication date).

properties.name: SpatialPoint
properties.description: A centroid point that reflects the locale of the content of the work product component (location of the subject matter).

properties.name: SpatialArea
properties.description: A polygon boundary that reflects the locale of the content of the work product component (location of the subject matter).

properties.name: SubmitterName
properties.description: Name of the person that first submitted the work product component to OSDU.

objecttypes.name: ChronoStratigraphy
objecttypes.description: The reference value type for Chronostratigraphic classification. The purpose of chronostratigraphic classification is to organize systematically the rocks forming the Earth's crust into named units (chronostratigraphic units) that represent intervals of geologic time (geochronologic units) to serve as references in narratives about Earth history including the evolution of life. Records of this kind represent chronostratigraphic units, i.e., bodies of rocks that include all rocks representative of a specific interval of geologic time, and only this time span. Chronostratigraphic units are bounded by isochronous horizons which mark specific moments of geological time. The rank (via data.ChronostratigraphicHierarchy) and relative magnitude of the units in the chronostratigraphic hierarchy are a function of the durations they represent.

properties.name: AgeBegin
properties.description: The age in million years at the beginning of the geochronologic interval.

properties.name: AgeEnd
properties.description: The age in million years at the end of the geochronologic interval.

properties.name: Colour
properties.description: Colour assigned to the geochronologic interval by the ICS (https://stratigraphy.org). The format is #RRGGBB where the colours are expressed as hex codes.

objecttypes.name: ChronoStratigraphySet
objecttypes.description: A set of references to ChronoStratigraphy reference data, which belong to the same StratigraphicColumnRankUnitType, e.g. "namespace:reference-data--StratigraphicColumnRankUnitType:Chronostratigraphic.System:" Only one of ChronoStratigraphySet or StratigraphicUnitInterpretationSet must be populated, never both.

properties.name: DateStamp
properties.description: Date curve was created in the database

properties.name: CurveVersion
properties.description: The Version of the Log Curve.

properties.name: CurveQuality
properties.description: The Quality of the Log Curve.

properties.name: InterpreterName
properties.description: The name of person who interpreted this Log Curve.

properties.name: IsProcessed
properties.description: Indicates if the curve has been (pre)processed or if it is a raw recording

properties.name: NullValue
properties.description: Indicates that there is no measurement within the curve

properties.name: DepthCoding
properties.description: DEPRECATED: Replaced by boolean data.IsRegular. The Coding of the depth.

properties.name: Interpolate
properties.description: Whether curve can be interpolated or not

properties.name: TopDepth
properties.description: The curve's minimum 'depth', i.e., the reference value at which the curve has its first non-absent value. The curve may contain further absent values in between TopDepth and BaseDepth. Note that the SamplingDomainType may not be a depth as the property name indicates.

properties.name: BaseDepth
properties.description: The curve's maximum 'depth' i.e., the reference value at which the curve has its last non-absent value. The curve may contain further absent values in between TopDepth and BaseDepth. Note that the SamplingDomainType may not be a depth as the property name indicates.

properties.name: DepthUnit
properties.description: Unit of Measure for TopDepth and BaseDepth.

properties.name: CurveUnit
properties.description: Unit of Measure for the Log Curve

properties.name: Mnemonic
properties.description: The Mnemonic of the Log Curve is the value as received either from Raw Providers or from Internal Processing team

properties.name: NumberOfColumns
properties.description: The number of columns present in this Curve for a single reference value. For simple logs this is typically 1; for image logs this holds the number of image traces or property series. Further information about the columns can be obtained via the respective log or curve APIs of the Domain Data Management Service.

properties.name: CurveDescription
properties.description: Mnemonic-level curve description is used during parsing or reading and ingesting LAS or DLIS files, to explain the type of measurement being looked at, specifically for that moment. Curve description is specific to that single (log) mnemonic and for the entire log (acquisition run) interval. In essence, curve description defines the internal factors such as what the "curve" or measurement ideally is representing, how is it calculated, what are the assumptions and the "constants".

properties.name: FacilityName
properties.description: Name of the Facility.

objecttypes.name: GeologicUnitInterpretation
objecttypes.description: Common properties for entities describing an opinion of a volume-based geologic feature or unit.

properties.name: IsIntrusive
properties.description: Corresponding to Energistics GeologicUnitMaterialEmplacement 'intrusive' and 'non-intrusive'.

objecttypes.name: GeologicUnitOccurrenceInterpretation
objecttypes.description:
Interpretation of a sequence of geologic units actually observed (interpreted)  along or inside a representation, the representation can be 
•	1D such as a well or an arbitrary line
•	2D like a cross section
•	3D like a entire model or a group of fault blocks
It is typically based on a stratigraphic column rank but can include more units (example intrusive bodies), duplicated units (repeated sequence along a well or lines), or less units (Eroded or non-deposited).
An ordering criteria indicates the reason for the order (age, apparent depth or measured depth).

objecttypes.name: GeologyIntervals
objecttypes.description: Set of geology and drilling information records for the wellbore. This is an API "data-node" query parameter for growing objects. See the relevant API specification for the query behavior related to this element.

properties.name: IntervalMeasuredDepthTop
properties.description: Measured depth at top of interval.

properties.name: IntervalMeasuredDepthBase
properties.description: Measured depth at base of interval.

properties.name: IntervalTVDTop
properties.description: True vertical depth at top of the section.

properties.name: IntervalTVDBase
properties.description: True vertical depth at base of interval.

properties.name: Description
properties.description: Description of item and details.

properties.name: ReferenceDatum
properties.description: Description of the Reference Datum used for Depth Measurement

objecttypes.name: HorizonInterpretation
objecttypes.description: Geologic information associated to horizon-related object types (marker, seismic picks, modeled objects etc…)

properties.name: isConformableAbove
properties.description: Defines whether the stratigraphic unit above the horizon is conformable

properties.name: isConformableBelow
properties.description: Defines whether the stratigraphic unit below the horizon is conformable

objecttypes.name: Interpretation
objecttypes.description: The group of properties shared by different kinds of interpretations

properties.name: OlderPossibleAge
properties.description: Represents the older possible age for the interpretation. Expressed in geological time as millions of years [Ma], and the value must be positive. The age value is not subject to normalization.

properties.name: YoungerPossibleAge
properties.description: Represents the younger possible age for the interpretation. Expressed in geological time as millions of years [Ma], and the value must be positive. The age value is not subject to normalization.

properties.name: FeatureName
properties.description: Name of the feature the Interpretation refers to

objecttypes.name: Interval
objecttypes.description: An interval given either by relationships to top/base markers or standalone top/base depths. To avoid confusion about entry and exit depths the naming convention uses Start as the entry point of the well path into the geologic unit and Stop as the exit point. For unfolded geologic units and vertical wellbores Start is Top and Stop is Base.

objecttypes.name: Intervals
objecttypes.description: Array of Intervals, index-aligned with IntervalProperties.

properties.name: StartMeasuredDepth
properties.description: The minimal MeasuredDepth of the interval. In the most common case this is the top.  If this value is associated with a marker then this value is a denormalization of data.Markers[].MarkerMeasuredDepth where the data.Markers[].MarkerID equals to StartMarkerID.

properties.name: StartSubSeaVerticalDepth
properties.description: True vertical depth sub-sea of the start of the interval. This is the same as true vertical depth referenced to the vertical CRS "MSL depth". If the start of the interval is associated with a marker then this value is a denormalization of data.Markers[].MarkerSubSeaVerticalDepth where the data.Markers[].MarkerID equals to StartMarkerID.

properties.name: StartIntervalName
properties.description: Name of the interval start (typically the top); when associated with a marker in a WellboreMarkerSet then this name is a denormalization of data.Markers[].MarkerName where the data.Markers[].MarkerID equals to StartMarkerID.

properties.name: StopMeasuredDepth
properties.description: The maximum MeasuredDepth of the interval (typically the base). If the interval stop is associated with a marker then this value is a denormalization of data.Markers[].MarkerMeasuredDepth where the data.Markers[].MarkerID equals to StopMarkerID.

properties.name: StopSubSeaVerticalDepth
properties.description: True vertical depth sub-sea of the interval stop (typically the base). This is the same as true vertical depth referenced to the vertical CRS "MSL depth". If the interval stop is associated with a marker then this value is a denormalization of data.Markers[].MarkerSubSeaVerticalDepth where the data.Markers[].MarkerID equals to StopMarkerID.

properties.name: StopIntervalName
properties.description: Name of the interval stop (typically the base); when associated with a marker in a WellboreMarkerSet then this name is a denormalization of data.Markers[].MarkerName where the data.Markers[].MarkerID equals to StopMarkerID.

objecttypes.name: LithologyType
objecttypes.description: Geological description for the type of lithology

objecttypes.name: LocalBoundaryFeature
objecttypes.description: An interface between two geological objects, such as horizons and faults in the scope of a model. It is a surface object. The scope can be widened by establishing a relationship to a master-data--BoundaryFeature instance.

objecttypes.name: LocalRockVolumeFeature
objecttypes.description: A volume of rock that is identified based on some specific attribute, like its mineral content or other physical characteristic. It exists typically in the scope of a model, can be associated with a master-data--RockVolumeFeature for regional correlations.

objecttypes.name: Marker
objecttypes.description: The array of marker meta data in this set.

properties.name: MarkerName
properties.description: Name of the Marker

properties.name: MarkerMeasuredDepth
properties.description: The depth at which the Marker was noted.

properties.name: MarkerSubSeaVerticalDepth
properties.description: The Marker's TVD converted to a Sub-Sea Vertical depth, i.e., below Mean Sea Level. Note that TVD values above MSL are negative. This is the same as true vertical depth referenced to the vertical CRS “MSL depth”.

properties.name: MarkerDate
properties.description: Timestamp of the date and time when the when the Marker was interpreted.

properties.name: MarkerObservationNumber
properties.description: Any observation number that distinguishes a Marker observation from others with same Marker name, date.

properties.name: MarkerInterpreter
properties.description: The name of the Marker interpreter (could be a person or vendor).

properties.name: FeatureName
properties.description: Name of the feature the marker is characterizing

properties.name: PositiveVerticalDelta
properties.description: The distance vertically above the Marker position that marks the limit of the high confidence range for the Marker pick.

properties.name: NegativeVerticalDelta
properties.description: The distance vertically below the Marker position that marks the limit of the high confidence range for the Marker pick.

properties.name: SurfaceDipAngle
properties.description: Dip angle for the Wellbore Marker.

properties.name: SurfaceDipAzimuth
properties.description: Dip azimuth for the Wellbore Marker.

properties.name: GeologicalAge
properties.description: Associated geological age

objecttypes.name: Markers
objecttypes.description: The array of marker meta data in this set. Markers are externally identified by data.Markers[].MarkerID, ideally a UUID. Older versions of the WellboreMarkerSet schema do not have this identifier. In this case, the string-converted array index is used as MarkerID. The the first index is "0".

objecttypes.name: PlannedLithology
objecttypes.description: Describes the sequence of expected lithologic intervals for the Wellbore

properties.name: WellName
properties.description: Human recognizable context for the well that contains the wellbore.

properties.name: WellboreName
properties.description: Human recognizable context for the wellbore that contains the mud log

properties.name: MeasuredDepthTop
properties.description: The minimum mdTop value for this object. This is an API "structural-range" query parameter for growing objects. See the relevant API specification for the query behavior related to this element.

properties.name: MeasuredDepthBase
properties.description: The maximum mdTop value for this object. This is an API "structural-range" query parameter for growing objects. See the relevant API specification for the query behavior related to this element.

objecttypes.description: Generic reference object containing the universal properties of reference data, especially the ones commonly thought of as Types

properties.name: Name
properties.description: The name of the entity instance.

properties.name: InactiveIndicator
properties.description: By default reference values are considered as 'active'. An absent 'InactiveIndicator' property value means the reference value is in active use. When 'InactiveIndicator' is set true the reverence value is no longer in use and should no longer be offered as a choice.

properties.name: Description
properties.description: The text which describes a NAME TYPE in detail.

properties.name: Code

properties.name: AttributionPublication

properties.name: AttributionRevision
properties.description: The distinct instance of the attribution publication, by version number, sequence number, date of publication, etc., that was used for the entity value.

properties.name: CommitDate
properties.description: For reference values published and governed by OSDU: The date and time the record was committed into the OSDU member GitLab reference-values repository. The sole purpose of this date is to optimise the OSDU milestone upgrades. It allows the upgrade code to figure out whether or not the record must be PUT into reference value storage.

objecttypes.name: SequenceStratigraphySurfaceType
objecttypes.description: Describes the horizon sequence stratigraphic information (flooding, ravinement, maximum flooding, transgressive).

objecttypes.name: StratigraphicColumn
objecttypes.description: Representation describing the vertical location of rock units in a particular area

properties.name: ValidationDate
properties.description: Date of validation of a custom stratigraphic column, start of validity

objecttypes.name: StratigraphicColumnRankInterpretation
objecttypes.description: A global hierarchy containing an ordered list of stratigraphic unit interpretations

objecttypes.name: StratigraphicColumnRankInterpretationSet
objecttypes.description: Array of StratigraphicColumnRankInterpretation[] the StratigraphicColumn is composed of

objecttypes.name: StratigraphicColumnRankUnitType
objecttypes.description: The reference value type defining a column position in a stratigraphic chart, which is ordered by rank (increasing from left to right).

properties.name: Rank
properties.description: The rank number of the column in the stratigraphic chart starting with 0 (=highest level in the hierarchy).

objecttypes.name: StratigraphicColumnValidityAreaType
objecttypes.description: Member where the custom stratigraphic column has been produced.

objecttypes.name: StratigraphicRoleType
objecttypes.description: The role or type of stratigraphy, e.g., Chronostratigraphic, Lithostratigraphic, etc.

objecttypes.name: StratigraphicUnitInterpretation
objecttypes.description: One of potentially many boundary interpretations as a single consistent description of a local boundary feature. An interpretation is subjective and very strongly tied to the intellectual activity of the project team members.

properties.name: MinimumThickness
properties.description: The minimum thickness of the StratigraphicUnitInterpretation.

properties.name: MaximumThickness
properties.description: The maximum thickness of the StratigraphicUnitInterpretation.

objecttypes.name: StratigraphicUnitInterpretationSet
objecttypes.description: Array of Stratigraphic Unit Interpretations the StratigraphicColumnRank is composed of. Units are ordered by ascending age or apparent depth.  Only one of ChronoStratigraphySet or StratigraphicUnitInterpretationSet must be populated, never both.

objecttypes.description: Generic reference object containing the universal group-type properties of a Work Product Component for inclusion in data type specific Work Product Component objects

properties.name: IsExtendedLoad
properties.description: A flag that indicates if the work product component is undergoing an extended load.  It reflects the fact that the work product component is in an early stage and may be updated before finalization.

properties.name: IsDiscoverable
properties.description: A flag that indicates if the work product component is searchable, which means covered in the search index.

objecttypes.name: WellLog
objecttypes.description: A well log is a data type that correlates a particular measurement or multiple measurements in a wellbore against depth and/or time within that wellbore. When plotted visually, well logs are typically long line graphs (called "curves") but may sometimes be discrete points or intervals. This schema object is intended for digital well logs, not raster log files or raster calibration files, but may be used for the latter in the absence of a defined OSDU schema for these use cases.

properties.name: TopMeasuredDepth
properties.description: Informational Top Measured Depth of the Well Log. Always populate SamplingStart and SamplingStop, which represents the real sampling of the WellLog, including  non-depth sampling.

properties.name: BottomMeasuredDepth
properties.description: Informational Bottom Measured Depth of the Well Log. Always populate SamplingStart and SamplingStop, which represents the real sampling of the WellLog, including  non-depth sampling.

properties.name: LogSource
properties.description: OSDU Native Log Source - will be updated for later releases - not to be used yet

properties.name: LogActivity
properties.description: Log Activity, used to describe the type of pass such as Calibration Pass - Main Pass - Repeated Pass

properties.name: LogRun
properties.description: Log Run - describe the run of the log - can be a number, but may be also a alphanumeric description such as a version name

properties.name: LogVersion
properties.description: Log Version

properties.name: LoggingService
properties.description: Logging Service - mainly a short concatenation of the names of the tools

properties.name: LogServiceDateInterval
properties.description: An interval built from two nested values : StartDate and EndDate. It applies to the whole log services and may apply to composite logs as [start of the first run job] and [end of the last run job]Log Service Date

properties.name: ToolStringDescription
properties.description: Tool String Description - a long concatenation of the tools used for logging services such as GammaRay+NeutronPorosity

properties.name: LoggingDirection
properties.description: Specifies whether curves were collected downward or upward

properties.name: PassNumber
properties.description: Indicates if the Pass is the Main one (1) or a repeated one - and it's level repetition

properties.name: DrillingFluidProperty
properties.description: Type of mud at time of logging (oil, water based,...)

properties.name: HoleTypeLogging
properties.description: Description of the hole related type of logging - POSSIBLE VALUE : OpenHole / CasedHole / CementedHole

properties.name: VerticalMeasurement
properties.description: The vertical measurement reference for the log curves, which defines the vertical reference datum for the logged depths. Either VerticalMeasurement or VerticalMeasurementID are populated.

properties.name: FrameIdentifier
properties.description: For multi-frame or multi-section files, this identifier defines the source frame in the file. If the identifier is an index number the index starts with zero and is converted to a string for this property.

properties.name: SamplingInterval
properties.description: For regularly sampled curves this property holds the sampling interval. For non regular sampling rate this property is not set. The IsRegular flag indicates whether SamplingInterval is required.

properties.name: SamplingStart
properties.description: The start value/first value of the ReferenceCurveID, typically the start depth of the logging.

properties.name: SamplingStop
properties.description: The stop value/last value of the ReferenceCurveID, typically the end depth of the logging.

properties.name: ZeroTime
properties.description: Optional time reference for (calender) time logs. The ISO date time string representing zero time. Not to be confused with seismic travel time zero. The latter is defined by SeismicReferenceDatum.

properties.name: SeismicReferenceElevation
properties.description: Populated only if the WellLog represents time-depth relationships or checkshots. It is expressed via the standard AbstractFacilityVerticalMeasurement. The following properties are expected to be present: VerticalMeasurementPathID (typically elevation), VerticalMeasurementTypeID as SeismicReferenceDatum, VerticalMeasurement holding the offset to either the VerticalCRSID or the chained VerticalReferenceID in the parent Wellbore.

properties.name: IsRegular
properties.description: Boolean property indicating the sampling mode of the ReferenceCurveID. True means all reference curve values are regularly spaced (see SamplingInterval); false means irregular or discrete sample spacing.

properties.name: LogRemark
properties.description: Log remark provides contextual information during the actual log object acquisition. Explains how the measurement in the wellbore is taken on a point in time or depth. Additional information may be included such as bad weather, tool failure, etc. Usually a part of the log header, log remark contains info specific for an acquisition run, specific for a given logging tool (multiple measurements) and/or a specific interval. In essence, log remark represents the external factors and operational environment, directly or indirectly affecting the measurement quality/uncertainty (dynamically over time/depth) - adding both noise and bias to the measurements.

objecttypes.name: WellboreIntervalSet
objecttypes.description: Define the geologic unit (including stratigraphic units) or fluid intervals along the wellbore, independent or based on markers  (defined in one or several WellboreMarkerSets).

properties.name: VerticalMeasurement
properties.description: References an entry in the Vertical Measurement array for the Wellbore identified by WellboreID, which defines the vertical reference datum for all marker measured depths of the WellboreIntervalSet Intervals array. It is strongly recommended specifying the VerticalMeasurement.WellboreTVDTrajectoryID  when SubSeaVerticalDepth are populated for the intervals.

properties.name: IntervalProperties
properties.description: An embedded ColumnBasedTable with the properties including their values associated to the intervals in data.Intervals[]. The association is done by array index.

objecttypes.name: WellboreMarkerSet
objecttypes.description: Wellbore Markers identify the depth in a wellbore, measured below a reference elevation, at which a person or an automated process identifies a noteworthy observation, which is usually a change in the rock that intersects that wellbore. Formation Marker data includes attributes/properties that put these depths in context. Formation Markers are sometimes known as picks or formation tops.

properties.name: VerticalMeasurement
properties.description: References an entry in the Vertical Measurement array for the Wellbore identified by WellboreID, which defines the vertical reference datum for all marker measured depths of the Wellbore Marker Set Markers array.

properties.name: FacilityName
properties.description: Name of the Facility.

objecttypes0.name: LocalRockVolumeFeature
objecttypes0.description: A volume of rock that is identified based on some specific attribute, like its mineral content or other physical characteristic. It exists typically in the scope of a model, can be associated with a master-data--RockVolumeFeature for regional correlations.

objecttypes0.name: PlannedLithology
objecttypes0.description: Describes the sequence of expected lithologic intervals for the Wellbore

properties.name: WellName
properties.description: Human recognizable context for the well that contains the wellbore.

properties.name: WellboreName
properties.description: Human recognizable context for the wellbore that contains the mud log

properties.name: MeasuredDepthTop
properties.description: The minimum mdTop value for this object. This is an API "structural-range" query parameter for growing objects. See the relevant API specification for the query behavior related to this element.

properties.name: MeasuredDepthBase
properties.description: The maximum mdTop value for this object. This is an API "structural-range" query parameter for growing objects. See the relevant API specification for the query behavior related to this element.

objecttypes0.name: SequenceStratigraphySurfaceType
objecttypes0.description: Describes the horizon sequence stratigraphic information (flooding, ravinement, maximum flooding, transgressive).

objecttypes0.name: StratigraphicColumn
objecttypes0.description: Representation describing the vertical location of rock units in a particular area

properties.name: ValidationDate
properties.description: Date of validation of a custom stratigraphic column, start of validity

objecttypes0.name: StratigraphicColumnRankInterpretation
objecttypes0.description: A global hierarchy containing an ordered list of stratigraphic unit interpretations

objecttypes0.name: StratigraphicUnitInterpretation
objecttypes0.description: One of potentially many boundary interpretations as a single consistent description of a local boundary feature. An interpretation is subjective and very strongly tied to the intellectual activity of the project team members.

properties.name: MinimumThickness
properties.description: The minimum thickness of the StratigraphicUnitInterpretation.

properties.name: MaximumThickness
properties.description: The maximum thickness of the StratigraphicUnitInterpretation.

objecttypes0.name: StratigraphicColumnRankInterpretationSet
objecttypes0.description: Array of StratigraphicColumnRankInterpretation[] the StratigraphicColumn is composed of

objecttypes0.name: StratigraphicUnitInterpretationSet
objecttypes0.description: Array of Stratigraphic Unit Interpretations the StratigraphicColumnRank is composed of. Units are ordered by ascending age or apparent depth.  Only one of ChronoStratigraphySet or StratigraphicUnitInterpretationSet must be populated, never both.

objecttypes0.name: StratigraphicColumnRankUnitType
objecttypes0.description: The reference value type defining a column position in a stratigraphic chart, which is ordered by rank (increasing from left to right).

properties.name: Rank
properties.description: The rank number of the column in the stratigraphic chart starting with 0 (=highest level in the hierarchy).

objecttypes0.name: StratigraphicRoleType
objecttypes0.description: The role or type of stratigraphy, e.g., Chronostratigraphic, Lithostratigraphic, etc.

objecttypes0.name: WellboreIntervalSet
objecttypes0.description: Define the geologic unit (including stratigraphic units) or fluid intervals along the wellbore, independent or based on markers  (defined in one or several WellboreMarkerSets).

properties.name: VerticalMeasurement
properties.description: References an entry in the Vertical Measurement array for the Wellbore identified by WellboreID, which defines the vertical reference datum for all marker measured depths of the WellboreIntervalSet Intervals array. It is strongly recommended specifying the VerticalMeasurement.WellboreTVDTrajectoryID  when SubSeaVerticalDepth are populated for the intervals.

properties.name: IntervalProperties
properties.description: An embedded ColumnBasedTable with the properties including their values associated to the intervals in data.Intervals[]. The association is done by array index.

objecttypes0.name: WellboreMarkerSet
objecttypes0.description: Wellbore Markers identify the depth in a wellbore, measured below a reference elevation, at which a person or an automated process identifies a noteworthy observation, which is usually a change in the rock that intersects that wellbore. Formation Marker data includes attributes/properties that put these depths in context. Formation Markers are sometimes known as picks or formation tops.

properties.name: VerticalMeasurement
properties.description: References an entry in the Vertical Measurement array for the Wellbore identified by WellboreID, which defines the vertical reference datum for all marker measured depths of the Wellbore Marker Set Markers array.

objecttypes0.name: ChronoStratigraphySet
objecttypes0.description: A set of references to ChronoStratigraphy reference data, which belong to the same StratigraphicColumnRankUnitType, e.g. "namespace:reference-data--StratigraphicColumnRankUnitType:Chronostratigraphic.System:" Only one of ChronoStratigraphySet or StratigraphicUnitInterpretationSet must be populated, never both.

objecttypes0.name: ChronoStratigraphy
objecttypes0.description: The reference value type for Chronostratigraphic classification. The purpose of chronostratigraphic classification is to organize systematically the rocks forming the Earth's crust into named units (chronostratigraphic units) that represent intervals of geologic time (geochronologic units) to serve as references in narratives about Earth history including the evolution of life. Records of this kind represent chronostratigraphic units, i.e., bodies of rocks that include all rocks representative of a specific interval of geologic time, and only this time span. Chronostratigraphic units are bounded by isochronous horizons which mark specific moments of geological time. The rank (via data.ChronostratigraphicHierarchy) and relative magnitude of the units in the chronostratigraphic hierarchy are a function of the durations they represent.

properties.name: AgeBegin
properties.description: The age in million years at the beginning of the geochronologic interval.

properties.name: AgeEnd
properties.description: The age in million years at the end of the geochronologic interval.

properties.name: Colour
properties.description: Colour assigned to the geochronologic interval by the ICS (https://stratigraphy.org). The format is #RRGGBB where the colours are expressed as hex codes.

objecttypes0.name: Markers
objecttypes0.description: The array of marker meta data in this set. Markers are externally identified by data.Markers[].MarkerID, ideally a UUID. Older versions of the WellboreMarkerSet schema do not have this identifier. In this case, the string-converted array index is used as MarkerID. The the first index is "0".

objecttypes0.name: Marker
objecttypes0.description: The array of marker meta data in this set.

properties.name: MarkerName
properties.description: Name of the Marker

properties.name: MarkerMeasuredDepth
properties.description: The depth at which the Marker was noted.

properties.name: MarkerSubSeaVerticalDepth
properties.description: The Marker's TVD converted to a Sub-Sea Vertical depth, i.e., below Mean Sea Level. Note that TVD values above MSL are negative. This is the same as true vertical depth referenced to the vertical CRS “MSL depth”.

properties.name: MarkerDate
properties.description: Timestamp of the date and time when the when the Marker was interpreted.

properties.name: MarkerObservationNumber
properties.description: Any observation number that distinguishes a Marker observation from others with same Marker name, date.

properties.name: MarkerInterpreter
properties.description: The name of the Marker interpreter (could be a person or vendor).

properties.name: FeatureName
properties.description: Name of the feature the marker is characterizing

properties.name: PositiveVerticalDelta
properties.description: The distance vertically above the Marker position that marks the limit of the high confidence range for the Marker pick.

properties.name: NegativeVerticalDelta
properties.description: The distance vertically below the Marker position that marks the limit of the high confidence range for the Marker pick.

properties.name: SurfaceDipAngle
properties.description: Dip angle for the Wellbore Marker.

properties.name: SurfaceDipAzimuth
properties.description: Dip azimuth for the Wellbore Marker.

properties.name: GeologicalAge
properties.description: Associated geological age

objecttypes0.name: Intervals
objecttypes0.description: Array of Intervals, index-aligned with IntervalProperties.

properties.name: StartMeasuredDepth
properties.description: The minimal MeasuredDepth of the interval. In the most common case this is the top.  If this value is associated with a marker then this value is a denormalization of data.Markers[].MarkerMeasuredDepth where the data.Markers[].MarkerID equals to StartMarkerID.

properties.name: StartSubSeaVerticalDepth
properties.description: True vertical depth sub-sea of the start of the interval. This is the same as true vertical depth referenced to the vertical CRS "MSL depth". If the start of the interval is associated with a marker then this value is a denormalization of data.Markers[].MarkerSubSeaVerticalDepth where the data.Markers[].MarkerID equals to StartMarkerID.

properties.name: StartIntervalName
properties.description: Name of the interval start (typically the top); when associated with a marker in a WellboreMarkerSet then this name is a denormalization of data.Markers[].MarkerName where the data.Markers[].MarkerID equals to StartMarkerID.

properties.name: StopMeasuredDepth
properties.description: The maximum MeasuredDepth of the interval (typically the base). If the interval stop is associated with a marker then this value is a denormalization of data.Markers[].MarkerMeasuredDepth where the data.Markers[].MarkerID equals to StopMarkerID.

properties.name: StopSubSeaVerticalDepth
properties.description: True vertical depth sub-sea of the interval stop (typically the base). This is the same as true vertical depth referenced to the vertical CRS "MSL depth". If the interval stop is associated with a marker then this value is a denormalization of data.Markers[].MarkerSubSeaVerticalDepth where the data.Markers[].MarkerID equals to StopMarkerID.

properties.name: StopIntervalName
properties.description: Name of the interval stop (typically the base); when associated with a marker in a WellboreMarkerSet then this name is a denormalization of data.Markers[].MarkerName where the data.Markers[].MarkerID equals to StopMarkerID.

properties.description: Name

properties.name: SubmitterName

objecttypes0.description: Member where the custom stratigraphic column has been produced.

objecttypes0.description: Set of geology and drilling information records for the wellbore. This is an API "data-node" query parameter for growing objects. See the relevant API specification for the query behavior related to this element.

properties.name: IntervalMeasuredDepthTop
properties.description: Measured depth at top of interval.

properties.name: IntervalMeasuredDepthBase
properties.description: Measured depth at base of interval.

properties.name: IntervalTVDTop
properties.description: True vertical depth at top of the section.

properties.name: IntervalTVDBase
properties.description: True vertical depth at base of interval.

properties.name: Description
properties.description: Description of item and details.

properties.name: ReferenceDatum
properties.description: Description of the Reference Datum used for Depth Measurement

objecttypes0.name: Interval
objecttypes0.description: An interval given either by relationships to top/base markers or standalone top/base depths. To avoid confusion about entry and exit depths the naming convention uses Start as the entry point of the well path into the geologic unit and Stop as the exit point. For unfolded geologic units and vertical wellbores Start is Top and Stop is Base.

objecttypes0.name: WellLog
objecttypes0.description: A well log is a data type that correlates a particular measurement or multiple measurements in a wellbore against depth and/or time within that wellbore. When plotted visually, well logs are typically long line graphs (called "curves") but may sometimes be discrete points or intervals. This schema object is intended for digital well logs, not raster log files or raster calibration files, but may be used for the latter in the absence of a defined OSDU schema for these use cases.

properties.name: TopMeasuredDepth
properties.description: Informational Top Measured Depth of the Well Log. Always populate SamplingStart and SamplingStop, which represents the real sampling of the WellLog, including  non-depth sampling.

properties.name: BottomMeasuredDepth
properties.description: Informational Bottom Measured Depth of the Well Log. Always populate SamplingStart and SamplingStop, which represents the real sampling of the WellLog, including  non-depth sampling.

properties.name: LogSource
properties.description: OSDU Native Log Source - will be updated for later releases - not to be used yet

properties.name: LogActivity
properties.description: Log Activity, used to describe the type of pass such as Calibration Pass - Main Pass - Repeated Pass

properties.name: LogRun
properties.description: Log Run - describe the run of the log - can be a number, but may be also a alphanumeric description such as a version name

properties.name: LogVersion
properties.description: Log Version

properties.name: LoggingService
properties.description: Logging Service - mainly a short concatenation of the names of the tools

properties.name: LogServiceDateInterval
properties.description: An interval built from two nested values : StartDate and EndDate. It applies to the whole log services and may apply to composite logs as [start of the first run job] and [end of the last run job]Log Service Date

properties.name: ToolStringDescription
properties.description: Tool String Description - a long concatenation of the tools used for logging services such as GammaRay+NeutronPorosity

properties.name: LoggingDirection
properties.description: Specifies whether curves were collected downward or upward

properties.name: PassNumber
properties.description: Indicates if the Pass is the Main one (1) or a repeated one - and it's level repetition

properties.name: DrillingFluidProperty
properties.description: Type of mud at time of logging (oil, water based,...)

properties.name: HoleTypeLogging
properties.description: Description of the hole related type of logging - POSSIBLE VALUE : OpenHole / CasedHole / CementedHole

properties.name: VerticalMeasurement
properties.description: The vertical measurement reference for the log curves, which defines the vertical reference datum for the logged depths. Either VerticalMeasurement or VerticalMeasurementID are populated.

properties.name: FrameIdentifier
properties.description: For multi-frame or multi-section files, this identifier defines the source frame in the file. If the identifier is an index number the index starts with zero and is converted to a string for this property.

properties.name: SamplingInterval
properties.description: For regularly sampled curves this property holds the sampling interval. For non regular sampling rate this property is not set. The IsRegular flag indicates whether SamplingInterval is required.

properties.name: SamplingStart
properties.description: The start value/first value of the ReferenceCurveID, typically the start depth of the logging.

properties.name: SamplingStop
properties.description: The stop value/last value of the ReferenceCurveID, typically the end depth of the logging.

properties.name: ZeroTime
properties.description: Optional time reference for (calender) time logs. The ISO date time string representing zero time. Not to be confused with seismic travel time zero. The latter is defined by SeismicReferenceDatum.

properties.name: SeismicReferenceElevation
properties.description: Populated only if the WellLog represents time-depth relationships or checkshots. It is expressed via the standard AbstractFacilityVerticalMeasurement. The following properties are expected to be present: VerticalMeasurementPathID (typically elevation), VerticalMeasurementTypeID as SeismicReferenceDatum, VerticalMeasurement holding the offset to either the VerticalCRSID or the chained VerticalReferenceID in the parent Wellbore.

properties.name: IsRegular
properties.description: Boolean property indicating the sampling mode of the ReferenceCurveID. True means all reference curve values are regularly spaced (see SamplingInterval); false means irregular or discrete sample spacing.

properties.name: LogRemark
properties.description: Log remark provides contextual information during the actual log object acquisition. Explains how the measurement in the wellbore is taken on a point in time or depth. Additional information may be included such as bad weather, tool failure, etc. Usually a part of the log header, log remark contains info specific for an acquisition run, specific for a given logging tool (multiple measurements) and/or a specific interval. In essence, log remark represents the external factors and operational environment, directly or indirectly affecting the measurement quality/uncertainty (dynamically over time/depth) - adding both noise and bias to the measurements.

properties.name: DateStamp
properties.description: Date curve was created in the database

properties.name: CurveVersion
properties.description: The Version of the Log Curve.

properties.name: CurveQuality
properties.description: The Quality of the Log Curve.

properties.name: InterpreterName
properties.description: The name of person who interpreted this Log Curve.

properties.name: IsProcessed
properties.description: Indicates if the curve has been (pre)processed or if it is a raw recording

properties.name: NullValue
properties.description: Indicates that there is no measurement within the curve

properties.name: DepthCoding
properties.description: DEPRECATED: Replaced by boolean data.IsRegular. The Coding of the depth.

properties.name: Interpolate
properties.description: Whether curve can be interpolated or not

properties.name: TopDepth
properties.description: The curve's minimum 'depth', i.e., the reference value at which the curve has its first non-absent value. The curve may contain further absent values in between TopDepth and BaseDepth. Note that the SamplingDomainType may not be a depth as the property name indicates.

properties.name: BaseDepth
properties.description: The curve's maximum 'depth' i.e., the reference value at which the curve has its last non-absent value. The curve may contain further absent values in between TopDepth and BaseDepth. Note that the SamplingDomainType may not be a depth as the property name indicates.

properties.name: DepthUnit
properties.description: Unit of Measure for TopDepth and BaseDepth.

properties.name: CurveUnit
properties.description: Unit of Measure for the Log Curve

properties.name: Mnemonic
properties.description: The Mnemonic of the Log Curve is the value as received either from Raw Providers or from Internal Processing team

properties.name: NumberOfColumns
properties.description: The number of columns present in this Curve for a single reference value. For simple logs this is typically 1; for image logs this holds the number of image traces or property series. Further information about the columns can be obtained via the respective log or curve APIs of the Domain Data Management Service.

properties.name: CurveDescription
properties.description: Mnemonic-level curve description is used during parsing or reading and ingesting LAS or DLIS files, to explain the type of measurement being looked at, specifically for that moment. Curve description is specific to that single (log) mnemonic and for the entire log (acquisition run) interval. In essence, curve description defines the internal factors such as what the "curve" or measurement ideally is representing, how is it calculated, what are the assumptions and the "constants".

properties.name: CommitDate
properties.description: For reference values published and governed by OSDU: The date and time the record was committed into the OSDU member GitLab reference-values repository. The sole purpose of this date is to optimise the OSDU milestone upgrades. It allows the upgrade code to figure out whether or not the record must be PUT into reference value storage.

properties.name: IsExtendedLoad
properties.description: A flag that indicates if the work product component is undergoing an extended load.  It reflects the fact that the work product component is in an early stage and may be updated before finalization.

properties.name: IsDiscoverable
properties.description: A flag that indicates if the work product component is searchable, which means covered in the search index.

properties.name: OlderPossibleAge
properties.description: Represents the older possible age for the interpretation. Expressed in geological time as millions of years [Ma], and the value must be positive. The age value is not subject to normalization.

properties.name: YoungerPossibleAge
properties.description: Represents the younger possible age for the interpretation. Expressed in geological time as millions of years [Ma], and the value must be positive. The age value is not subject to normalization.

properties.name: FeatureName
properties.description: Name of the feature the Interpretation refers to

properties.name: id
properties.description: Previously called ResourceID or SRN which identifies this OSDU resource object without version.

properties.name: kind
properties.description: The schema identification for the OSDU resource object following the pattern {Namespace}:{Source}:{Type}:{VersionMajor}.{VersionMinor}.{VersionPatch}. The versioning scheme follows the semantic versioning, https://semver.org/.

properties.name: version
properties.description: The version number of this OSDU resource; set by the framework.

properties.name: acl
properties.description: The access control tags associated with this entity.

properties.name: legal
properties.description: The entity's legal tags and compliance status. The actual contents associated with the legal tags is managed by the Compliance Service.

properties.name: tags
properties.description: A generic dictionary of string keys mapping to string value. Only strings are permitted as keys and values.

properties.name: createTime
properties.description: Timestamp of the time at which initial version of this OSDU resource object was created. Set by the System. The value is a combined date-time string in ISO-8601 given in UTC.

properties.name: createUser
properties.description: The user reference, which created the first version of this resource object. Set by the System.

properties.name: modifyTime
properties.description: Timestamp of the time at which this version of the OSDU resource object was created. Set by the System. The value is a combined date-time string in ISO-8601 given in UTC.

properties.name: modifyUser
properties.description: The user reference, which created this version of this resource object. Set by the System.

properties.name: ancestry
properties.description: The links to data, which constitute the inputs.

properties.name: Name
properties.description: Name

properties.name: Description
properties.description: Description.  Summary of the work product component.  Not the same as Remark which captures thoughts of creator about the wpc.

properties.name: CreationDateTime
properties.description: Date that a resource (work  product component here) is formed outside of OSDU before loading (e.g. publication date).

properties.name: SpatialPoint
properties.description: A centroid point that reflects the locale of the content of the work product component (location of the subject matter).

properties.name: SpatialArea
properties.description: A polygon boundary that reflects the locale of the content of the work product component (location of the subject matter).

properties.name: SubmitterName
properties.description: Name of the person that first submitted the work product component to OSDU.

properties.name: isConformableAbove
properties.description: Defines whether the stratigraphic unit above the horizon is conformable

properties.name: isConformableBelow
properties.description: Defines whether the stratigraphic unit below the horizon is conformable

properties.name: WellName
properties.description: Human recognizable context for the well that contains the wellbore.

properties.name: WellboreName
properties.description: Human recognizable context for the wellbore that contains the mud log

properties.name: MeasuredDepthTop
properties.description: The minimum mdTop value for this object. This is an API "structural-range" query parameter for growing objects. See the relevant API specification for the query behavior related to this element.

properties.name: MeasuredDepthBase
properties.description: The maximum mdTop value for this object. This is an API "structural-range" query parameter for growing objects. See the relevant API specification for the query behavior related to this element.

properties.name: ValidationDate
properties.description: Date of validation of a custom stratigraphic column, start of validity

properties.name: Rank
properties.description: The rank number of the column in the stratigraphic chart starting with 0 (=highest level in the hierarchy).

properties.name: MinimumThickness
properties.description: The minimum thickness of the StratigraphicUnitInterpretation.

properties.name: MaximumThickness
properties.description: The maximum thickness of the StratigraphicUnitInterpretation.

properties.name: IsIntrusive
properties.description: Corresponding to Energistics GeologicUnitMaterialEmplacement 'intrusive' and 'non-intrusive'.

properties.name: VerticalMeasurement
properties.description: References an entry in the Vertical Measurement array for the Wellbore identified by WellboreID, which defines the vertical reference datum for all marker measured depths of the WellboreIntervalSet Intervals array. It is strongly recommended specifying the VerticalMeasurement.WellboreTVDTrajectoryID  when SubSeaVerticalDepth are populated for the intervals.

properties.name: IntervalProperties
properties.description: An embedded ColumnBasedTable with the properties including their values associated to the intervals in data.Intervals[]. The association is done by array index.

properties.name: VerticalMeasurement
properties.description: References an entry in the Vertical Measurement array for the Wellbore identified by WellboreID, which defines the vertical reference datum for all marker measured depths of the Wellbore Marker Set Markers array.

properties.name: IntervalMeasuredDepthTop
properties.description: Measured depth at top of interval.

properties.name: IntervalMeasuredDepthBase
properties.description: Measured depth at base of interval.

properties.name: IntervalTVDTop
properties.description: True vertical depth at top of the section.

properties.name: IntervalTVDBase
properties.description: True vertical depth at base of interval.

properties.name: Description
properties.description: Description of item and details.

properties.name: ReferenceDatum
properties.description: Description of the Reference Datum used for Depth Measurement

objecttypeviews.name: c7030ab4-9a11-47fc-df41-1ecce93b90d1
objecttypeviews.description:
Interpretation of a sequence of geologic units actually observed (interpreted)  along or inside a representation, the representation can be 
•	1D such as a well or an arbitrary line
•	2D like a cross section
•	3D like a entire model or a group of fault blocks
It is typically based on a stratigraphic column rank but can include more units (example intrusive bodies), duplicated units (repeated sequence along a well or lines), or less units (Eroded or non-deposited).
An ordering criteria indicates the reason for the order (age, apparent depth or measured depth).

objecttypeviews.description: Define the geologic unit (including stratigraphic units) or fluid intervals along the wellbore, independent or based on markers  (defined in one or several WellboreMarkerSets).

objecttypeviews.name: eda42b0d-f679-4c22-05ce-d148977c7571
objecttypeviews.description: Wellbore Markers identify the depth in a wellbore, measured below a reference elevation, at which a person or an automated process identifies a noteworthy observation, which is usually a change in the rock that intersects that wellbore. Formation Marker data includes attributes/properties that put these depths in context. Formation Markers are sometimes known as picks or formation tops.

objecttypeviews.name: 6061133e-55e7-45e8-7d68-1209922c49f7
objecttypeviews.description: A set of references to ChronoStratigraphy reference data, which belong to the same StratigraphicColumnRankUnitType, e.g. "namespace:reference-data--StratigraphicColumnRankUnitType:Chronostratigraphic.System:" Only one of ChronoStratigraphySet or StratigraphicUnitInterpretationSet must be populated, never both.

objecttypeviews.name: 2d07df00-a001-4972-10a5-fc584a838826
objecttypeviews.description: The reference value type for Chronostratigraphic classification. The purpose of chronostratigraphic classification is to organize systematically the rocks forming the Earth's crust into named units (chronostratigraphic units) that represent intervals of geologic time (geochronologic units) to serve as references in narratives about Earth history including the evolution of life. Records of this kind represent chronostratigraphic units, i.e., bodies of rocks that include all rocks representative of a specific interval of geologic time, and only this time span. Chronostratigraphic units are bounded by isochronous horizons which mark specific moments of geological time. The rank (via data.ChronostratigraphicHierarchy) and relative magnitude of the units in the chronostratigraphic hierarchy are a function of the durations they represent.

objecttypeviews.name: 39c55b75-49f3-4756-3d2d-20424c0ca26f
objecttypeviews.description: The array of marker meta data in this set. Markers are externally identified by data.Markers[].MarkerID, ideally a UUID. Older versions of the WellboreMarkerSet schema do not have this identifier. In this case, the string-converted array index is used as MarkerID. The the first index is "0".

objecttypeviews.name: 0a39ba06-5acd-4a8f-eec8-1acb25e16607
objecttypeviews.description: Set of geology and drilling information records for the wellbore. This is an API "data-node" query parameter for growing objects. See the relevant API specification for the query behavior related to this element.

objecttypeviews.name: 41dde113-6652-4d5a-fca2-158cdcd8df76
objecttypeviews.description: An interval given either by relationships to top/base markers or standalone top/base depths. To avoid confusion about entry and exit depths the naming convention uses Start as the entry point of the well path into the geologic unit and Stop as the exit point. For unfolded geologic units and vertical wellbores Start is Top and Stop is Base.

objecttypeviews.name: a9388d23-7f6f-4116-33d7-cc5ffb89e47d
objecttypeviews.description: A well log is a data type that correlates a particular measurement or multiple measurements in a wellbore against depth and/or time within that wellbore. When plotted visually, well logs are typically long line graphs (called "curves") but may sometimes be discrete points or intervals. This schema object is intended for digital well logs, not raster log files or raster calibration files, but may be used for the latter in the absence of a defined OSDU schema for these use cases.
